@node AdvancedOptions "More information"

Magic Colors can be controlled also via@{b} Workbench Tooltypes @{ub}or by giving parameters on command line. These settings override the general configuration in@{b} ENV: @{ub}and@{b} ENVARC:@{ub}.

                               · Tooltypes ·

CX_PRIORITY
CX_POPUP
CX_POPKEY
	These are explained in your AmigaOS manual (default is "lcommand lshift g")

STARTCOLOR	(Format: STARTCOLOR=RGB)
	Hexadecimal RGB-value of color for the top of the screen

ENDCOLOR	(Format: ENDCOLOR=RGB)
	Hexadecimal RGB-value of color for the bottom of the screen

NUMCOLORS	(Format: NUMCOLORS=2 to NUMCOLORS=16)
	Number of steps used in the slide; value is decimal

                        · Command line arguments ·

Template:

CX_PRIORITY/N/K,CX_POPUP/K,CX_POPKEY/K,C1=COLOR1,C2=COLOR2,N=NUM/N/K

Mostly same as tooltypes, COLOR1 is STARTCOLOR ad COLOR2 is ENDCOLOR.

@endnode
